                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Nose Hill Park, situated just outside of Dalhousie, is one of the most significant amenities available to the residents of this beautiful community.</p>
                    <p>In Canada, Nose Hill Park is a one-of-a-kind urban park. With natural grasslands, old archaeological sites, sweeping views of the cityscape, and wildlife spanning from gophers to moose, this 2700-acre sanctuary is a great source of pride for its neighbouring communities and a fantastic destination to escape to. The park has 8 kilometres of concrete walkways that connect it to the city's local pathways.</p>
                    <p>Another major attraction for the Dalhousie community is the Community Association.</p>
                    <p>The Dalhousie Community Association provides a variety of services for residents of this Northwestern community, including a playgroup and playschool, kindergarten, and Kindermusik. A dynamic and healthy community spirit is ensured through Girl Guides and Boy Scouts, as well as a range of sports, fitness, and activities for both children and adults. The Crowfoot YMCA, Edgemont's World Health Club, and the Sir Winston Churchill Aquatic & Recreation Centre are all close, as are playgrounds, playing fields, and golf courses.</p>
                    <p>Other activities you can engage in as a resident of Dalhousie include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">Shopping at Market Mall and other major shopping centres, all of which are only a short drive from the community.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">Homesense, The Bay, Sporting Life, Zara, and a slew of other well-known retailers can be found here.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">Shopping at the Northland Village Mall, which is located just to the East of Dalhousie.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">The community is centrally located and is connected to all major roadways and the city centre via Shaganappi Trail and other easily accessible routes.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
