        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>Dalhousie, named after George Ramsay, the 9th Earl of Dalhousie, was founded in 1967.</p>
            <p>Dalhousie had a census of 9,085 people living in 3,739 homes in the 2012 municipal census, up 1.9% from its 2011 demographic of 8,917.</p>
            <p>In 2000, residents in this neighbourhood had a median family income of $59,298 and 17.1% of families were considered to be low-income. Immigrants made up 24.1% of the population in 2000. Condominiums or apartments accounted for 25.1% of the structures. While 26.8% of the housing was rented, the remaining houses were occupied by their owners.</p>
            <p>The community's median age is 38.6 years, while the median age for the rest of Calgary is 37.4 years. Dalhousie has an average of 2.5 persons per family and a near-equal gender ratio of 50% female and male residents. A whopping 17% of the residents of Dalhousie are above the age of 65, compared to 10% for the rest of Calgary.</p>
            <p>There are many detached single-family homes in the area that come in various styles. A traditional bungalow, a retro 2-storey house, condominiums, and townhouses are all readily available. Condos in Dalhousie are getting increasingly popular as a result of the facilities available.</p>
            <p>With less than 9,000 people, the neighbourhood is small yet picturesque, with beautiful parks and children's playgrounds.</p>
